<Window x:Class="VidFileTag.HelpWindow"
        xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
        xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
        xmlns:d="http://schemas.microsoft.com/expression/blend/2008"
        xmlns:mc="http://schemas.openxmlformats.org/markup-compatibility/2006"
        xmlns:local="clr-namespace:VidFileTag"
        mc:Ignorable="d"
        Title="HelpWindow"  Width="804">

    <FlowDocumentScrollViewer Background="#FFF1F3F7" BorderBrush="Purple" BorderThickness="3" >
            <FlowDocument    Background="#FFF1F3F7" ColumnWidth="400" 
                                   IsOptimalParagraphEnabled="True"  >
           
                <BlockUIContainer >
                    <Button Content="Close Help" 
                                Margin="2" HorizontalAlignment="Right" Foreground="Purple"
                               VerticalAlignment="Top" x:Name="HelpClose" Click="HelpClose_Click" />
                </BlockUIContainer>
            <Paragraph >
                <Bold>VidFileTag Help</Bold>
                <LineBreak/>
            </Paragraph>
            <Paragraph>
                VidFileTag is a program that is used to add tags to media files of many kinds, images, music, and vidieo. 
                    It maintains all tag information in a local own database and never modifies media files.
                    Operations like copying all files tagged with a particualar tag to a location, or 
                    saving a playlist of files with a selected set of tags are available. 
                    Tagging copies of files tagged in another location is another job the VidFileTag cam perform.
                    VidFileTag has a media player to allow viewing or listining to media file to help chose tags.
                    The VideoLan.LibVLC.Windows media library is used.

             </Paragraph>
           
            <Paragraph>
                    <Figure  TextAlignment="Left"  HorizontalAnchor="ContentLeft">
                        <Paragraph Margin="1">

                            Tag and other operations use the files in the current directory.

                        </Paragraph>
                        <BlockUIContainer BorderBrush="Purple" BorderThickness="1">
                            <StackPanel>
                                <Border BorderBrush="Purple" BorderThickness="2">
                                    <StackPanel>
                                        <Label Target="{Binding ElementName=PathChoiceImage}" BorderBrush="Purple" BorderThickness="1">
                                            <TextBlock Text="Set Target Directory" />
                                        </Label>
                                        <Image x:Name="PathChoiceImage" 
                                        Visibility="Visible"  Source="DirectoryToll.png" />
                                    </StackPanel>
                                </Border>
                            </StackPanel>
                        </BlockUIContainer>
                        <Paragraph  Margin="1">
                            <Run>
                                To Set the current directory location use three controls, 
                                        the "disk drive selector" to choose a disk drive,
                                        , a mouse "click on a child directory" in the list of child directorys to move to that child. 
                                        and the "up arrow" to move to the parent of the current directory.
                            </Run>
                            <LineBreak/>
                            <Run>
                                The current directory path is shown above the
                            "Up" arrow.

                            </Run>
                        </Paragraph>
                    </Figure>
                </Paragraph>

                <Paragraph>
                    <Figure 
                             
                               TextAlignment="Left" 
                                 HorizontalAnchor="ContentLeft">
                        <Paragraph Margin="1" >

                            Tags selected in the 'Tag Selection" area may be associated in the database with 
                                the currently selected file using "Add Tags" or the association may be removed with "Remove Tags"
                            <LineBreak/>
                            Pressing the 'List Files with Tag' button will list all file 
                                associated with a selected tag.

                        </Paragraph>
                        <BlockUIContainer BorderBrush="Purple" BorderThickness="1">
                            <StackPanel>
                                <Border BorderBrush="Purple" BorderThickness="2">
                                    <StackPanel>
                                        <Label Target="{Binding ElementName=PathChoiceImage}" BorderBrush="Purple" BorderThickness="1">
                                            <TextBlock Text="The tags list and basic operations" />
                                        </Label>
                                        <Image x:Name="BasicTagImage" MaxWidth="450"
                                        Visibility="Visible"  Source="BasicTagOperations.png" />
                                    </StackPanel>
                                </Border>
                            </StackPanel>
                        </BlockUIContainer>
                        <Paragraph  Margin="1">
                            Type in tag creation and press "Create Tag" to create a tag and add it to the database.
                                
                                Select a tag in the 'Tag Selection' list when it is the only selected tag it will show in the 
                                Tag Operations area and may be deleted using "Delete Tag" or if differing text is input may be 
                                modified using the "Update Tag" button.

                        </Paragraph>
                    </Figure>
                </Paragraph>

                <Paragraph>
                    <Figure 
                              
                               TextAlignment="Left" 
                                 HorizontalAnchor="ContentLeft">
                        <BlockUIContainer BorderBrush="Purple" BorderThickness="1">

                            <Border BorderBrush="Purple" BorderThickness="2">
                                <StackPanel>
                                    <Label Target="{Binding ElementName=FileListImage}" BorderBrush="Purple" BorderThickness="1">
                                        <TextBlock Text="All Media Shown" />
                                    </Label>
                                    <Image x:Name="FileListImage"  Margin="3" 
                                             Visibility="Visible"  Source="mediaListOne.png" />
                                </StackPanel>
                            </Border>

                        </BlockUIContainer>
                        <Paragraph  Margin="1">

                            Files in the current directory are listed in the media file list. 
                                        Pressing the "Show all Media files" button will show all file.

                        </Paragraph>
                    </Figure>
                </Paragraph>


                <Paragraph>
                    <Figure>
                        <BlockUIContainer  BorderBrush="Purple" BorderThickness="1">
                            <Border  BorderBrush="Purple" BorderThickness="2">
                                <StackPanel>
                                    <Label Target="{Binding ElementName=FileWildImage}" BorderBrush="Purple" BorderThickness="1">
                                        <TextBlock Text="Show media with 'bach' " />
                                    </Label>
                                    <Image x:Name="FileWildImage"  Margin="3"
                                        Visibility="Visible"  Source="WildCardfILES7.png" Width="380"/>
                                </StackPanel>
                            </Border>
                        </BlockUIContainer>
                        <Paragraph  Margin="1">
                            The list can also filtered using a simple pattern like
                            <Italic>*text*</Italic>

                        </Paragraph>
                    </Figure>
                </Paragraph>


                <Paragraph>
                    <Figure>
                        <BlockUIContainer  BorderBrush="Purple" BorderThickness="1">
                            <Border BorderBrush="Purple" BorderThickness="2">
                                <StackPanel>
                                    <Label Target="{Binding ElementName=FileTagImage}" BorderBrush="Purple" BorderThickness="1">
                                        <TextBlock Text="Tag in file media shown" />
                                    </Label>
                                    <Image x:Name="FileTagImage" Margin="3"
                                                Visibility="Visible"  Source="TagSearcgFiles1.png" />
                                </StackPanel>
                            </Border>
                        </BlockUIContainer>
                        <Paragraph  Margin="1">
                            The list can also show only files that have selected tags in their filename.

                        </Paragraph>
                    </Figure>
                </Paragraph>



                <Paragraph>

                    <Figure   
                               TextAlignment="Left" 
                                 HorizontalAnchor="ContentLeft">
                        <BlockUIContainer BorderBrush="Purple" BorderThickness="1">
                            <StackPanel>
                                <Border BorderBrush="Purple" BorderThickness="2">
                                    <StackPanel>
                                        <Label Target="{Binding ElementName=AfterFileSelect}" BorderBrush="Purple" BorderThickness="1">
                                            <TextBlock Text="When Media Selected" />
                                        </Label>
                                        <Image x:Name="AfterFileSelect"  Margin="3" 
                                             Visibility="Visible"  Source="AfterMediaSelected.png" />
                                    </StackPanel>
                                </Border>
                            </StackPanel>
                        </BlockUIContainer>
                        <Paragraph  Margin="1">
                            When a file is selected in the file list The file names is displayed in the Selected file box and any 
                            tags in the database for that file instance are shown also. If the file is a media file media 
                            information is displayed in the File information area.
                          
                        </Paragraph>
                    </Figure>


                </Paragraph>

            <Paragraph>

                <Figure   
                               TextAlignment="Left" 
                                 HorizontalAnchor="ContentLeft">
                    <BlockUIContainer BorderBrush="Purple" BorderThickness="1">
                        <StackPanel>
                            <Border BorderBrush="Purple" BorderThickness="2">
                                <StackPanel>
                                    <Label Target="{Binding ElementName=MediaPlayerImage}" BorderBrush="Purple" BorderThickness="1">
                                        <TextBlock Text="Media player window" />
                                    </Label>
                                    <Image x:Name="MediaPlayerImage"  Margin="3" 
                                             Visibility="Visible"  Source="vidieoshed.png" />
                                </StackPanel>
                            </Border>
                        </StackPanel>
                    </BlockUIContainer>
                    <Paragraph  Margin="1">
                       
                        If the file is a media file and "Play" in the media control is pressed a media player window appears and 
                            the media plays. 
                    </Paragraph>
                </Figure>


            </Paragraph>

        </FlowDocument>
        </FlowDocumentScrollViewer>
   
</Window>
